\ Logical binrec levels grow independently of the VM frame stack.
5000 [ 0 == ] [ drop 0 ] [ pred 0 ] [ + ] binrec 0 == check

\ Exercise binrec's heap fallback with more ambient stack values than its
\ inline rollback snapshot can hold.
0 33 range 10 push-back
[ [ 2 < ] [ ] [ pred dup pred ] [ + ] binrec ] infra
0 33 range 55 push-back == check

\ An error during the first recursive branch releases a heap fallback snapshot
\ and restores the stack seen by try.
0 33 range 10 push-back [
    [
        [ dup 2 == [ "binrec rollback" error ] if 2 < ]
        [ ]
        [ pred dup pred ]
        [ + ]
        binrec
    ] [ drop ] try
] infra
0 33 range == check

[ 1 [ 2 3 ] 4 ] [ ] [ 0 swap [ + ] fold ] treerec
10 == check

\ Exercise treerec's heap fallback with a deep ambient stack.
0 33 range [ 1 [ 2 3 ] 4 ] push-back
[ [ ] [ ] treerec ] infra
0 33 range [ 1 [ 2 3 ] 4 ] push-back == check

\ Nested oversized snapshots use separate scratch blocks and unwind in LIFO
\ order through an error handler.
0 600 range [
    1 [
        [ "scratch unwind" error ] [ ] try
    ] dip drop
] infra
0 600 range == check

\ Oversized predicate snapshots share the same scoped scratch storage.
0 600 range [
    [ 1 2 3 ] [ 0 > ] some not [ "scratch predicate" error ] if
] infra
0 600 range == check
